The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Sri Lanka recall Arnold 

Colombo: Sri Lanka have recalled middle-order batsman Russel Arnold for their tour of New Zealand. Left-hander Arnold, 31, was dropped in July, but has fought his way back into the one-day squad. 

THE SQUAD 

Maravan Atapattu (captain), Mahela Jayawardene (vice-captain), Kumar Sangakkara, Sanath Jayasuriya, Chaminda Vaas, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Russel Arnold, Saman Jayantha, Muttiah Muralidharan, Upul Chandana, Nuwan Zoysa, Farveez Maharoof, Dilhara Fernando, Nuwan Kulasekera, Rangana Herath, 

Test specialists: Ian Daniel, Thilan Samaraweera, Lasith Malinga 

Note: Muttiah Muralidharan will be touring with the squad but will not be playing the initial matches. (Reuters) 

